JRuby classes generated by "jrubyc" are different that generated by "jrubyc --javac".
If you want to implement Java inteface in JRuby use "jrubyc --javac" command instead of "jrubyc".

[1 case]
jrubyc --javac:
public class SimpleImplementation extends RubyObject implements SimpleJavaInterface { (...) }

[2 case]
jrubyc:
public class SimpleImplementation extends AbstractScript { (...) }

[2 case] generete error:
"incompatible types" for code:

SimpleJavaInterface sji = new SimpleImplementation();



=====================================================
 how to run code:
=====================================================
	update variables in run.sh
	bash run.sh



...
